en you let your tank build up some agro, but you don't heal him.  Once he gets below two bubbles he starts running and of course the mob will chase him mindlessly forever.  Everyone else just smacks the mob from behind.  If you know the zone and refine your technique you can take some very difficult mobs like this.  The nice thing is that unlike a fear, you control the direction of the mob so avoiding adds becomes a lot easier.  If you take a few hits a couple spot heals will ensure you don't get too low.<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uxvailtrueblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xvail TrueBlade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 3:43:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15143.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aye!</span><hr size=1> ok i am confused now, some of you agree with me and some of you say i am wrong. main question:<br><br>When flashed, does the mob keep running till it is hit by YOU, or does it keep going until someone else moves to the top of its hate list. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujcasetn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jcasetn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/3/02 4:13:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15143.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: aye!</span><hr size=1> I was in akhevia the other day and I fol'd a mob by accident when I hit the wrong gem.  It just took off.  It blew right by 